---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="About — Roberto Bautista"
  description="Roberto Bautista — AI Product Manager. A decade from operations and growth into product; now building AI products that ship and get adopted."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-12 pb-24 sm:pt-24">
    <h1 class="mb-8 text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">About</h1>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
      <p>
        I'm Roberto — an AI Product Manager at SoftServe. I help enterprises turn AI from
        pilots into products that ship and get adopted, owning the path from an ambiguous
        problem to a measurable outcome across several client streams at once. I think like a
        <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">product strategist</strong> and work like a
        <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">builder</strong>: close to the customer,
        biased toward shipping.
      </p>
      <p>
        I didn't start in product, and that's shaped how I work. Over the last decade I climbed
        from front-line operations at a Fortune-100 contact-center partner, into growth —
        building a startup's first sales team and growing revenue 5× — and then into product at
        Crabi, a digital car insurer, where I shipped the MVP that cut claim times up to 5×.
        Every step was a <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">problem to solve</strong>
        and a new craft to learn — which is the throughline: a
        <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">growth mindset</strong>, real
        <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">curiosity</strong>, and the willingness to
        put in the <strong class="font-medium text-foreground">hard, unglamorous work</strong>
        to make something real.
      </p>
      <p>
        Today I'm all-in on AI product, and on staying hands-on with the craft rather than just
        managing it. I'm deepening production GenAI system design and practicing a spec-driven,
        agentic software workflow — this very site is built that way, end to end. I'd rather
        understand how a thing works than admire it from a distance.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of work, I'm a husband and dad to two kids — a daily lesson in prioritization,
        patience, and doing a lot with limited time. Based in Guadalajara, México; I studied at
        ITESO.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
